<br>
I took a Shaman, a Cleric, and a couple Wizards with me to HoH, and to the inner caves of PoV, and this pet TANKS, baby.<br>
<br>
Obviously, any melee in the group would immediately take aggro once in proximity, but if you're ever short-handed, or you want to do something &quot;different&quot;, this pet is a great Warrior.<br>
<br>
With Shaman buffs, summoned armor, Cleric buffs and etceteras, this pet handled everything we threw at him.<br>
<br>
Watching him GRAB the incoming mob was hilarious, as he'd spin it around and start beating on it, as the puller whizzed by.<br>
<br>
This pet isn't the solo panacea, but then I've pretty much given up on the idea of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>efficient</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> soloing at this point.<br>
<br>
Great addition to a caster group, however.  Want some XP?  Head to BoT with Muddy, and a Shaman.  Add DPS casters liberally. <br>
<br>
No melee need apply.  =)<br>
<br>
