<br>
You may be right.<br>
<br>
That is, I haven't tested this to any great extent, because I normally have, at the least, a Shaman with me, or a Bard/Cleric combo.<br>
<br>
I cannot comment on the reliability of the root, yet, as I've not done appropriate sampling to make any justifiable comments.<br>
<br>
As for my definition of &quot;efficient soloing&quot; I would define that as soloing with low risk to the Mage, with enough blue or low-blue MOBs incoming to minimize downtime, and soloing which doesn't cause enough drain on mana to force overly long downtime. <br>
<br>
For example, at level 60 I used to get an AA every 2 hours in Katta using epic pet, and was never out of MOBs and there was very little risk. <br>
<br>
I define overly-long downtime as anything over a couple of minutes.    <br>
<br>
What I can say about the Earth pet in PoP zones like HoH, BoT, and PoV is that without slow, this pet gets chewed so fast that I believe soloing would not be effective, and would be very dangerous.  In PoN it is much more viable on light blues, but the XP there stinks, at 65.<br>
<br>
I'd be very interested to hear from other Mages who use this pet as a soloing tool, and do so efficiently.<br>
<br>
